This paper discusses the ethical development and governance of AI, which falls under the category of AI. The paper also touches upon issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and legal and professional accountability mechanisms (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the translation of principles into practice, which could be related to the category of ethics and technology (cs.ET). Finally, the paper mentions the lack of common aims and fiduciary duties in AI development, which could be related to the category of robotics (cs.RO).
